  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">What remains of this letter is two fragments, enclosed in one piece of mylar. Lucia Weston says that Mr. L. read her a letter from Mrs. Lydia Maria Child. At present, Mrs. Child is devoted to &quot;[William?] Page the Painter,&quot; who is thought to have consumption. Lucia Weston repeats a witty &quot;dig at Garrison&quot; by Mrs. Child, who derided his predilection for preambles.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Enclosed, is a separate sheet of paper that identifies these letter fragments as: &quot;Extract from a letter of Lucia Weston&apos;s, dated Weymouth, July 3rd, 1849.&quot;</subfield>
